captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]

JESSE WELLENS: I'm about
to go HAM, son.

Dope Fresh Nation, try and find
that in the performance,

because I'm bringing
you guys with me.

I really want to win to
impress my viewers.

I really want to do
this for them.
I just want the title.

I feel it's bigger
than the money.

But trust me, the money is
great, that's awesome.

If I was to win the money, it
would definitely speed up the

process of putting a little
shiny thing on Jeana's finger

and maybe a really
dope wedding.

Yeah, so the last performance,
I messed up a little bit.
I showed it in my face.
Joey caught it.
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]
-You messed up a little bit.

And I saw that because if you
didn't show your face, I would

have never known that
you messed up.
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

JESSE WELLENS: Called
me out, so I know--
keep my eye on the prize.

No matter what happens, keep
my face ready to go.

LAUREN FRODERMAN: We're
a minute away.
And we just want to go.

PRANKVSPRANK: Yes, we get out
there and kill it, go do it.

DOMINIC SANDOVAL: Performing
next-- please give it up for

PrankvsPrank, partnered
with Lauren Froderman.

[MUSIC - FAR EAST MOVEMENT,
"TURN UP THE LOVE (FEAT.
COVER DRIVE)"]
[APPLAUSE]

DOMINIC SANDOVAL: Jesse, how
are you feeling, my man?
JESSE WELLENS: I feel awesome.

I feel like I really did
what I wanted to do.

I went out there and killed
it, went HAM, son.
DOMINIC SANDOVAL: All right.

Ryan Higa, how are
you feeling?

RYAN HIGA: You were just
so into it, you
just sold it for me.

Probably my favorite dance that
I've seen on this show so
far, for me.
And you just did so well.

I know there was a little
mess-up with the
lift at that one time.

I don't even know what part
of the song that was.

But I didn't even care because
you just played it off like it
was natural.

You played if off and
just kept going.
And you just killed it for me.
It was great.
DOMINIC SANDOVAL: Well done.
All right, Joey Fatone?

JOEY FATONE: Loved the energy,
loved a lot of the stuff that

you guys were dancing
together.

If I would've never known that
there was a challenge to have

a lift for eight counts,
I would've never
known you messed up.

And the reason why I say that--
because it was eight

counts that she was
off the ground.

Because it looked like you were
about to step, she missed
her footing somewhere.

And it kinda looked cool
because in my mind, I'm

thinking, OK, is this part of--
oh no, I think it was a
little mess-up.

But it looked like she was
trying to get in the club.

And you were like, no, get
the hell off my back.

JESSE WELLENS: That's what I was
thinking when it happened.

She taught me, just
keep going.

And you taught me, don't make
a face like you did.

JOEY FATONE: And that's why
I commend you for it.

But that's the greatest thing,
you didn't make a face, you
didn't let it show.

And for people that are
watching, they would never
notice that.

And for me, we just did just
due to the fact that D-trix

came up with this eight
count lift challenge.

Also, like I said, I think
it was really good.

There was a couple little
moments I thought was a little

sporadic, a tiny bit, but
nothing too crazy.
You guys were on point.
And the story was really cool.

I don't think I've ever seen a
story come out with a club.
And it's cool, I liked it.
Really a lot of fun.
DOMINIC SANDOVAL: Cool.
Nice.
Two for two.
Laurieann?

LAURIEANN GIBSON:
Holy [BLEEP].
Am I allowed to say that?
Oh, [BLEEP], I said it.
Oh my god.

Oh my god, Prank, that was
a freaking showdown.

You're making my
life difficult.

Just when I thought I saw what
was going to be my number one

choice, you came and you
discombobulated the truth.

You put me in the Ring
of Confusion.
That was amazing!
I'm so excited.
Because here's the thing, never
have I seen this concept.
Super clever.

But to pull it off,
you two, really?

Momma's smelling a
little greatness.

Very difficult to tell that
story through movement.
Do you know what I'm saying?

And yet you told it
effortlessly, and you
entertained me.
And you danced your ass off.

Then the eight count you did,
when you came down, was way

above the first bit of
choreography that you did the

first time you were
on the show.

You did a real eight
count, son.
It was hip hop.

And that's when I was
like, showdown!
Ahhh!
OK?

Just excited, because it
was really original.
Finale, you brought it.

And Blondie, oh my
God, that whole
through his legs, really?
JESSE WELLENS: That's crazy.

LAURIEANN GIBSON:
The audacity.

And she danced at such a level
that, for you to keep up with,
was brilliant.

Because this girl can
dance, seriously.
And she brought it for you.
And you brought it for her.

And please, you're fine in that
black and white suit.
JESSE WELLENS: Thank you.
Thank you.

DOMINIC SANDOVAL: I think you're
only half of Prank.

You have another half of
PrankvsPrank, right, Jeana?
Come in and join your man.

Listen, you were telling me
earlier, Jeana, that he was
just nonstop last night.

Just going over and practicing,
and practicing.
JEANA: In the shower.
He was dancing in the shower.
LAURIEANN GIBSON: What?

JEANA: There's a screen
in the shower, and I
could see his head.

JOEY FATONE: Well, real quick--
what goes through your

mind right before you're
about to perform?

Because you've never really done
this as a professional,

as far as thinking, going
out and dancing.

JESSE WELLENS: Just don't think
about it, let my body do
the motions.

I felt like my body knows now,
and it will just tell me what
to do next.

So I stopped thinking
about it.

But that's what my problem
was, was overthinking it.
And I overthank--
thunk it?
Thunk it? thunk it?

DOMINIC SANDOVAL: You
overthunk it.

JESSE WELLENS: --thunk it,
on our last performance.

And that's why I think
I slipped up.
I got nervous.
DOMINIC SANDOVAL: Nice.

JOEY FATONE: Well, you did a
great job as far as what we've

said, if something messes
up, just keep on going.
You don't even think about it.

LAUREN FRODERMAN: I
can't express--

more commitment than I've seen
in some professionals.

I am so proud, bursting
with pride.

DOMINIC SANDOVAL:
Well done, man.

Congratulations to you both,
and good luck, man.
We'll see you guys later.
Jeana, thanks for joining us.
Take care, guys.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
